<Base
  title="Flight Experience Audit — Meish"
  description="Meish's human-state method, adapted to the passenger journey — load, recovery, presence and afterglow, from the gate to arrival."
>
  <section class="section container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Aviation · On-journey</p>
    <h1>The same question, at 38,000 feet: what happened in the passenger?</h1>
    <p class="lead">Meish brings its human-state method to the passenger journey — from the
      gate to the seat to the arrival. We read load, recovery, presence, and afterglow where
      most airline metrics only read punctuality and throughput.</p>

    <h2>What we look at</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The pre-boarding and boarding state — stress, crowding, uncertainty</li>
      <li>In-seat recovery — can a passenger actually settle?</li>
      <li>Crew micro-attachments — the small moments that change a whole flight</li>
      <li>Arrival afterglow — how the journey lands, emotionally</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What you get</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>A passenger-journey friction map</li>
      <li>Ranked, crew-workable fixes</li>
      <li>An improvement plan calibrated to your cabin and route</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The lane, honestly</h2>
    <p>Before a carrier pilot, this runs as the Meish method — a parallel to the Clara model,
      not a separate public brand. We won't claim carrier results we haven't earned.</p>

    <p><a class="button button--primary" href="/contact">Talk about a pilot</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
